        "  SGD rebalancing degrades significantly with imbalance ratio c.\n"
        "  This confirms: ortho(c*M) = ortho(M) makes Muon scale-invariant.")
elif muon_is_Olog and muon_always_faster and (sgd_rate_drops or sgd_never_halves):
    verdict = "PARTIAL PASS"
    verdict_summary = (
        "Muon rebalancing time is O(log c), NOT O(1) as originally predicted.\n"
        "  The O(1) prediction assumed ortho invariance alone suffices, but\n"
        "  the step-size-to-weight-norm ratio lr/||W|| still matters: the\n"
        "  orthogonal update has unit norm while ||W1|| = c*sqrt(d), so\n"
        "  each step reduces log_imbalance by O(lr/(c*sqrt(d))).\n"
        "  However, Muon is MUCH faster than SGD at all c values.\n"
        "  SGD's reduction rate degrades more steeply with c.\n"
        "  The DIRECTION invariance (ortho(c*G)=ortho(G)) is real and helpful,\n"
        "  even if it does not yield strict O(1) rebalancing.")
elif muon_always_faster:
